sql:
SELECT COUNT(p.patient_id) AS patient_count
FROM patients p
JOIN maternity_births mb ON p.patient_id = mb.patient_id
WHERE p.ethnicity = 'African American' AND mb.birth_weight > (
  SELECT AVG(birth_weight) FROM maternity_births
);

external_knowledge:
- "Follow-up visits" are subsequent visits by patients who have already been seen at the clinic before;
- "Initial records" refer to the first patient records created, typically when a patient first visits the clinic;
- "Updated records" are records that have been modified or updated after the initial creation.

- "first bloom of health seekers" refers to the first visit of patients to a clinic;
- "medical garden" is a metaphor for the location of the clinic;
